  "prompt": "Is it bad to take Plan B, the morning after pill, multiple times?",
  "response": "Taking Plan B, or other emergency contraception, multiple times is not recommended as a regular form of birth control. While it's safe for most people to use emergency contraception more than once, it is designed for occasional use. Frequent use can lead to irregular menstrual cycles and may not be as effective compared to regular birth control methods.\n\nIf you find yourself needing emergency contraception regularly, it may be a good idea to consult with a healthcare provider about more reliable and consistent forms of birth control that suit your needs. They can provide guidance on the most appropriate methods for you.",
